      • Split

        public void Split(Node node)
        Parameters:
        node - parent node

        the method initializes the four sons of the parent node with the appropriate coordinates, checks to which of the four sons the figures from the parent node belong, it inserts them correspondingly and then erases figures from parent node

      • Insert

        public boolean Insert(Node node,
                      GeometricObject x)
        Parameters:
        node - node which is tested for insert; starts from tree root
        x - object to be inserted
        Returns:
        true or false, depending on whether the insertion has ended successfully or not

        if the node is a leaf with no objects in it, insert x and return true

        if node to be tested is not a leaf, then check to which of the for children the object belongs and call insert on the appropriate node

        if node to be tested has objects in its array, then check if x collides with any of the figures already belonging to the node. if not, then split the node and call insert on the appropriate children; else insert directly into the node

        root - display tree starting from root

      • SearchPoint

        public void SearchPoint(double x,
                        double y,
                        Node node,
                        Array rez)
        Parameters:
        x - abscissa of point to be tested
        y - ordinate of point to be tested
        node - node to be tested
        rez - array which contains the ID-s of the figures to which the point belongs

        if node to be tested has no figures in its array and no children, then return

        if node to be tested is not a leaf: check to which of the four children the point belongs and call SearchPoint on the appropriate son

        if node to be tested has figures in its array: for each instance of geometric objects (circle, rhombus, rectangle and triangle), call the corresponding VerifyPoint method from each class to check if the point belongs to the figure; if the result is positive, add the id of the figure to the rez array

      • TestCollision

        public void TestCollision(GeometricObject x,
                          Node node,
                          Array v)
        Parameters:
        x - figure to be tested
        node - node to be tested
        v - array to store the id-s of the figures which collide with the given figure x

        if node is leaf and has no children return;

        if node has children, but no figures in its array (thus, it is a parent for other nodes): check to which of the four sons the figure x belongs and continue searching in the appropriate quadrants

        if node to be tested has figures: for each figure in the array of figures check if x and the current figure collide by calling the Collision method from the Geometric object class; if the answer is true, add the id of the current figure

      • Delete

        public void Delete(GeometricObject x,
                   Node node,
                   Node parent)
        Parameters:
        x - object to be deleted
        node - node to be tested
        parent - parent of node to be tested

        if node to be tested is null return

        if node to be tested has no objects in its array: search in the children to which the figure x belongs

        if the node has figures in its node: search amongst them for the figure to be deleted and erase it if it is found.

      • Remake

        void Remake(Node parent)
        Parameters:
        parent - node from which the remake of the tree starts

        if node to be tested or its children are null return;

        if none of the children of the node have figures in their arrays, then erase the nodes

        if only one of the four children has figures in its array and the others do not: copy the figures in the array of the parent and erase the nodes

        if all four nodes contain the same figures: copy them into the parent and erase the nodes

        continue searching in the children of the node
